Enabling Auto-login for Linux Lite v1.0.0 - 1.0.4

Two methods to choose from:

Method 1:

1. Open a terminal, type in the following:

gksu lxdm-config
Place a tick in 'Automatic Login'

Next time you reboot you will auto-login.

Method 2:

2. Open a terminal, type in the following:

sudo leafpad /etc/lxdm/lxdm.conf

At line 3 remove the # from the start of the line, put your login name after the = sign and save the file.
Next time you reboot, you will automatically login.
